<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; From&#58; Alan Sill &#60;Alan.Sill@....&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Date&#58; April 25, 2006 10&#58;00&#58;25 AM EDT<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; To&#58; Frederick Luehring &#60;luehring@....&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Cc&#58; Matthew Norman &#60;mnorman@....&#62;, Tim Silvers  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; &#60;tsilver@....&#62;, Alan Sill &#60;Alan.Sill@....&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Subject&#58; Re&#58; 1803 TTU-ANTAEUS Site Policy Inquiry - ISSUE=1803<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; The ticket essentially resolves into two components&#58;  (1) based on  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; the title and initial inquiry, the question was &#34;what VOs are  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; allowed to run on TTU-ANTAEUS?&#34;  This can be resolved, and the  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; snwer is as follows&#58; we advertise support for USCMS only but accept  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; jobs from all OSG VOs.  The particular problem Matthew reported was  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; not based on policy, but was due to a self-denial-of-service of his  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; jobs that brought down our NFS-based home directory system on this  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; cluster.<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; This leads to (2) the question of how Matthew (and CDF) should be  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; writing their jobs to take advantage of the OSG environmental  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; variables to run on local worker node directories to avoid this  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; problem across OSG in general.  I believe this was covered in  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; personal responses, but am not sure whether this led to  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; improvements to documentation in this area.  This portion should  <br></font>
<div id='show_6420626' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_6420626'><font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; not be considered closed unless this is checked.  An auxiliary  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; topic that grew out of this point was increased attention to the  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; document being circulated on &#34;NFS Lite&#34; cluster configuration  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; techniques for OSG clusters by Frank Wuerthwein and company.  We  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; have not had an opportunity to apply all of these methods yet to  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; the antaeus cluster, or to determine whether this would have solved  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Matthew&#39;s problems.  It would be interesting to know whether and if  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; so how these recommendations, or the lessons learned from this  <br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; problem, will affect CDF job submission practices and / or OSG policy.<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Alan<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; On Apr 25, 2006, at 7&#58;16 AM, Frederick Luehring wrote&#58;<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;<br></font>
