<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; statically  assigned WN_TMP area. If instead that WN_TMP was assigned<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; a variable  value (eg. $OSG_WN_TMP=$_CONDOR_SCRATCH with condor) that<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; is then  expanded in the jobs shell then you could have the job land<br></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; in the exact  same spot as specified by OSG_WN_TMP.<br></font>
